about.summary: A system for 'declaratively' creating graphics, based on "The Grammar of Graphics". You provide the data, tell 'ggplot2' how to map variables to aesthetics, what graphical primitives to use, and it takes care of the details.

name: r-ggplot2
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "3.3.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggplot2
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggplot2_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggplot2/ggplot2_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a03a3e37d9945adf7ce28995f5a9a59487ad346e9762675fb2c267da14d79b13

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-glue
    - r-gtable >=0.1.1
    - r-isoband
    - r-mass
    - r-mgcv
    - r-rlang >=0.3.0
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-tibble
    - r-withr >=2.0.0
  run:
    - r-base

    - r-digest
    - r-glue
    - r-gtable >=0.1.1
    - r-isoband
    - r-mass
    - r-mgcv
    - r-rlang >=0.3.0
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-tibble
    - r-withr >=2.0.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggplot2')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggplot2')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://ggplot2.tidyverse.org, https://github.com/tidyverse/ggplot2
  license: GPL-2
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2
  summary: A system for 'declaratively' creating graphics, based on "The Grammar of Graphics". You provide the data, tell 'ggplot2' how to map variables to aesthetics, what graphical primitives to use, and it takes care of the details.
  license_family: GPL2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ocefpaf
    - philip-khor
